      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Dave Gomboc</b>\n</p><p><b>David (Dave) Ross Gomboc</b>,<br />\na Canadian computer scientist and <a href=\"/Artificial_Intelligence\" title=\"Artificial Intelligence\">AI</a> researcher affiliated with <a href=\"/AAAI\" title=\"AAAI\">AAAI</a>, <a href=\"/ACM\" title=\"ACM\">ACM</a>, <a href=\"/ICGA\" title=\"ICGA\">ICGA</a> and <a href=\"/IEEE\" title=\"IEEE\">IEEE</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and the <a href=\"/University_of_Southern_California\" title=\"University of Southern California\">University of Southern California</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>. His research interests include <a href=\"/Automated_Tuning\" title=\"Automated Tuning\">automatic tuning</a> of <a href=\"/Evaluation\" title=\"Evaluation\">evaluation functions</a>, which was also topic of his 2004 masters thesis at <a href=\"/University_of_Alberta\" title=\"University of Alberta\">University of Alberta</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>. In 2000, Dave Gomboc serverd as moderator in <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>.  \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dave_Gomboc&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Dave Gomboc</a>, <a href=\"/Tony_Marsland\" title=\"Tony Marsland\">Tony Marsland</a>, <a href=\"/Michael_Buro\" title=\"Michael Buro\">Michael Buro</a> (<b>2003</b>). <i>Evaluation Function Tuning via Ordinal Correlation</i>. <a href=\"/Advances_in_Computer_Games_10\" title=\"Advances in Computer Games 10\">Advances in Computer Games 10</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Dave Gomboc</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Tuning Evaluation Functions by Maximizing Concordance</i>. M.Sc. Thesis, <a href=\"/University_of_Alberta\" title=\"University of Alberta\">University of Alberta</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Dave Gomboc</a>, <a href=\"/Michael_Buro\" title=\"Michael Buro\">Michael Buro</a>, <a href=\"/Tony_Marsland\" title=\"Tony Marsland\">Tony Marsland</a> (<b>2005</b>). <i>Tuning Evaluation Functions by Maximizing Concordance</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theoretical_Computer_Science_%28journal%29\">Theoretical Computer Science</a>, Vol. 349, No. 2, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cs.ualberta.ca/%7Emburo/ps/tcs-learn.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Dave Gomboc</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Christian_R._Shelton&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Christian R. Shelton (page does not exist)\">Christian R. Shelton</a> (<b>2021</b>). <i>Chess endgame compression via logic minimization</i>. <a href=\"/Advances_in_Computer_Games_17\" title=\"Advances in Computer Games 17\">Advances in Computer Games 17</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dave_Gomboc&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=22053\">1998 WCCC and/or WMCCC sponsorship</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Dave Gomboc</a>,  <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 11, 1998</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=45304\">full-ply search extension leads to crash city!</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Dave Gomboc</a>,  <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 07, 1999&#160;» <a href=\"/Extensions\" title=\"Extensions\">Extensions</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=54343\">Re: negascout vs pvs</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Dave Gomboc</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 04, 1999&#160;» <a href=\"/NegaScout\" title=\"NegaScout\">NegaScout</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=14963&amp;start=27\">Re: iterative deepening and branching factor</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Dave Gomboc</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 24, 2009&#160;» <a href=\"/Iterative_Deepening\" title=\"Iterative Deepening\">Iterative Deepening</a>, <a href=\"/Branching_Factor#EffectiveBranchingFactor\" title=\"Branching Factor\">Effective Branching Factor</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=27266&amp;start=12\">Re: Insanity... or Tal style?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Dave Gomboc</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 02, 2009&#160;» <a href=\"/Automated_Tuning\" title=\"Automated Tuning\">Automated Tuning</a> in <a href=\"/Gaviota\" title=\"Gaviota\">Gaviota</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dave_Gomboc&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cs.ucr.edu/~gomboc//\">Minimalist Home Page of Dave Gomboc</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=xUrivMsAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">‪Dave Gomboc‬ - ‪Google Scholar‬</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dave_Gomboc&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cs.ucr.edu/~gomboc//\">Minimalist Home Page of Dave Gomboc</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Dave Gomboc</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Christian_R._Shelton&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Christian R. Shelton (page does not exist)\">Christian R. Shelton</a> (<b>2021</b>). <i>Chess endgame compression via logic minimization</i>. <a href=\"/Advances_in_Computer_Games_17\" title=\"Advances in Computer Games 17\">Advances in Computer Games 17</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Dave Gomboc</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Tuning Evaluation Functions by Maximizing Concordance</i>. M.Sc. Thesis, <a href=\"/University_of_Alberta\" title=\"University of Alberta\">University of Alberta</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/g/Gomboc:Dave.html\">dblp: Dave Gomboc</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260228123743\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.009 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.010 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 75/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 166/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key oscar70_mw1-mw_:pcache:idhash:6382-0!canonical and timestamp 20260228123743 and revision id 26051\n -->\n"
